post_text: Starting today September 8, 2020 students of the Southwest School District will be able to receive both breakfast and lunch at no cost. This is an offering as part of a USDA waiver to extend the Seamless Summer program. This program will be offered until December 31, 2020. Current lunch balances will be held until after December 31, no action needs to be taken by parents to take part in this program. More information regarding the program will be posted on the website and and sent home with students.

post_text: My last official duty for Southwest School before I retire was to present one of my predecessors with a well deserved award! Franklin E. Schottel was recently honored by the Missouri Association of School Administrators for his service to public education. Mr. Schottel was one of eight former educators to receive the association‚Äôs Outstanding Emeritus Educator Award, and was the Northwest Region‚Äôs nominee. Thank you Mr. Schottel for your years of service and dedication to Southwest School! I also want to say thank you to the board of education and patrons of the district for allowing me the privilege of serving as the district‚Äôs superintendent for the past seven years. I will miss everyone , but I feel confident I am leaving the district in the very capable hands of Burnie Schneiderheinze!

post_text: The Southwest FCCLA delivered 370 "Stuffies for Seniors" to local senior facilities recently. Mrs. Neptune and her students shared the donated stuffed animals and dolls with residents of Golden Age Nursing Home in Braymer, and Livingston Manor, The Baptist Home, Morningside Center, Grand River Health Care and Indian Hills all in Chillicothe. While visiting, the students got to say hello to a couple of longtime Wildcat supporters! Job well done, FCCLA!

post_text: The Southwest Livingston Co R1 Board of Education reorganized last evening for the 2019-2020 school year. Outgoing board member Mark Anderson receives a plaque from Supt Cindy Barnes for his 9 years of service to the board. Board Secretary Carrie Gilliland administers the Oath of Office to Re-elected board member Bryce Anderson and newly elected member Clint Gilliland. Bryce Anderson was later elected President of the Board with Charles Jones elected Vice President, Carrie Gilliland Secretary and Orland Oesch Treasurer. Other members include Laura Warren-Hughes, Chasity Anderson and Tyler Anderson.

post_text: Proud of our Wildcat Spellers! Southwest sent 10 elementary students to the CLAA Spelling Bee held yesterday at Bosworth. Mariel Allen took 2nd Place in 2nd grade while Kylie Kirtland took 1st Place in 6th. Other contestants included Lark Diegelman 2nd, Elias Allen 3rd (not pictured), Maci Mohr 3rd, Gavin Farris 4th, Jacey Hall 4th, Jessalie Trent 5th, Amber Adams 5th, and Mylee Waters 6th. Congratulations!

post_text: The Southwest School yearbook staff has yearbooks from the following years for sale: 1983-1987, 1990, 1992, 1996, & 2003-2018. Books from 2003 and newer will be $30 and anything older than 2003 will be $5. Please contact Ms. Terhune at kterhune@southwestr1.org or (660)738-4433 if you would like to purchase any of these yearbooks!
